$ Office Object Model: Word - MailMergeDataSource

A `MailMergeDataSource` → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/object specifies the *data source* for a → Microsoft/Office/Word/Object-Model/MailMerge[mail merge] or *catalog merge* operation.

A `MailMergeDataSource` → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/object is returned by the → Microsoft/Office/Word/Object-Model/MailMerge#word-mailMerge-dataSource[`mailMerge.dataSource`] property.

{ connectString

  The `connectString` specifies the data source.

  A `connectString` to get → development/Data from → Microsoft/Office/Excel might be
code {
Provider=Microsoft.ACE.OLEDB.12.0;User ID=Admin;Data Source=P:\ath\to\excel\workbook.xlsx;Mode=Read;Extended Properties="HDR=YES;IMEX=1;";Jet OLEDB:System database="";Jet OLEDB:Registry Path="";Jet OLEDB:Engine Type=37;Jet OLEDB:Database Locking Mode=0;Jet OLEDB:Global Partial Bulk Ops=2;Jet OLEDB:Global Bulk Transactions=1;Jet OLEDB:New Database Password="";Jet OLEDB:Create System Database=False;Jet OLEDB:Encrypt Database=False;Jet OLEDB:Don't Copy Locale on Compact=False;Jet OLEDB:Compact Without Replica Repair=False;Jet OLEDB:SFP=False;Jet OLEDB:Support Complex Data=False;Jet OLEDB:Bypass UserInfo Validation=False;Jet OLEDB:Limited DB Caching=False;Jet OLEDB:Bypass ChoiceField Validation=False
code }

}

sa:
  → Microsoft/Office/Word/Object-Model
